# `junit-jupiter` aggregator artifact

[JUnit 5.4 provides][1] much simpler Maven configuration if your intent is to write JUnit 5 tests. Simply specify the aggregate artifact named [`junit-jupiter`][2]. 

&lt;!-- language: lang-xml --&gt;

    &lt;!-- https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.junit.jupiter/junit-jupiter --&gt;
    &lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.junit.jupiter&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;junit-jupiter&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;5.9.1&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;


As an aggregate, this artifact in turn pulls the following three artifacts automatically, for your convenience:

 - [`junit-jupiter-api`][3] (a compile dependency)
 - [`junit-jupiter-params`][4]  (a compile dependency)
 - [`junit-jupiter-engine`][5]  (a runtime dependency)

In your project, you will also end up with:

 - junit-platform-commons-1.4.0.jar
 - junit-platform-engine-1.4.0.jar

The above is what you need to **write and run JUnit 5 tests** based on the new Jupiter paradigm.

# Legacy tests

If your project has JUnit 3 or 4 tests that you want to continue to run, add another dependency for the *JUnit Vintage Engine*, [`junit-vintage-engine`][6]. See [tutorial by IBM][7].

&lt;!-- language: lang-xml --&gt;

    &lt;!-- https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.junit.vintage/junit-vintage-engine --&gt;
    &lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.junit.vintage&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;junit-vintage-engine&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;5.9.1&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;


  [1]: https://hub.packtpub.com/junit-5-4-released-with-an-aggregate-artifact-for-reducing-your-maven-and-gradle-files/
  [2]: https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.junit.jupiter/junit-jupiter
  [3]: https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.junit.jupiter/junit-jupiter-api
  [4]: https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.junit.jupiter/junit-jupiter-params
  [5]: https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.junit.jupiter/junit-jupiter-engine
  [6]: https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.junit.vintage/junit-vintage-engine
  [7]: https://developer.ibm.com/tutorials/j-introducing-junit5-part2-vintage-jupiter-extension-model/

